    {
      "content": "On the top menu, click Applications, and then click the application you want to configure.",
      "pos": [
        11696,
        11786
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The Quick Start page will appear with single sign-on and other configuration information.",
      "pos": [
        11787,
        11876
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Click on the Manage manifest button in the command bar, and select Download manifest.",
      "pos": [
        11881,
        11966
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Open the JSON application manifest file and replace “oauth2Permissions” node with the following JSON snippet.",
      "pos": [
        11971,
        12080
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This snippet is an example of how to expose a permission scope known as user impersonation, make sure that you change the text and values for your own application:",
      "pos": [
        12081,
        12244
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The id value must be a new generated GUID that you create by using a GUID generation tool or programmatically.",
      "pos": [
        12919,
        13029
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "It represents a unique identifier for the permission that is exposed by the web API.",
      "pos": [
        13030,
        13114
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Once your client is appropriately configured to request access to your web API and calls the web API, it will present an OAuth 2.0 JWT token that has the scope (scp) claim set to the value above, which in this case is user_impersonation.",
      "pos": [
        13115,
        13352
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">[AZURE.NOTE]</ph> You can expose additional permission scopes later as necessary.",
      "pos": [
        13359,
